40 /*
41 ================
42 return a hash value for the filename
43 ================
44 */
45 #ifdef __GNUCC__
46  #warning TODO: check if long is ok here
47 #endif
48 static long generateHashValue( const char *fname, const int size ) {
49  int i;
50  long hash;
51  char letter;
52 
53  hash = 0;
54  i = 0;
55  while (fname[i] != '\0') {
56  letter = tolower(fname[i]);
57  if (letter =='.') break; // don't include extension
58  if (letter =='\\') letter = '/'; // damn path names
59  if (letter == PATH_SEP) letter = '/'; // damn path names
60  hash+=(long)(letter)*(i+119);
61  i++;
62  }
63  hash = (hash ^ (hash >> 10) ^ (hash >> 20));
64  hash &= (size-1);
65  return hash;
66 }

68 void R_RemapShader(const char *shaderName, const char *newShaderName, const char *timeOffset) {
69  char strippedName[MAX_QPATH];
70  int hash;
71  shader_t *sh, *sh2;
72  qhandle_t h;
73 
74  sh = R_FindShaderByName( shaderName );
75  if (sh == NULL || sh == tr.defaultShader) {
76  h = RE_RegisterShaderLightMap(shaderName, 0);
77  sh = R_GetShaderByHandle(h);
78  }
79  if (sh == NULL || sh == tr.defaultShader) {
80  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: R_RemapShader: shader %s not found\n", shaderName );
81  return;
82  }
83 
84  sh2 = R_FindShaderByName( newShaderName );
85  if (sh2 == NULL || sh2 == tr.defaultShader) {
86  h = RE_RegisterShaderLightMap(newShaderName, 0);
87  sh2 = R_GetShaderByHandle(h);
88  }
89 
90  if (sh2 == NULL || sh2 == tr.defaultShader) {
91  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: R_RemapShader: new shader %s not found\n", newShaderName );
92  return;
93  }
94 
95  // remap all the shaders with the given name
96  // even tho they might have different lightmaps
97  COM_StripExtension(shaderName, strippedName, sizeof(strippedName));
98  hash = generateHashValue(strippedName, FILE_HASH_SIZE);
99  for (sh = hashTable[hash]; sh; sh = sh->next) {
100  if (Q_stricmp(sh->name, strippedName) == 0) {
101  if (sh != sh2) {
102  sh->remappedShader = sh2;
103  } else {
104  sh->remappedShader = NULL;
105  }
106  }
107  }
108  if (timeOffset) {
109  sh2->timeOffset = atof(timeOffset);
110  }
111 }

113 /*
114 ===============
115 ParseVector
116 ===============
117 */
118 static qboolean ParseVector( char **text, int count, float *v ) {
119  char *token;
120  int i;
121 
122  // FIXME: spaces are currently required after parens, should change parseext...
123  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
124  if ( strcmp( token, "(" ) ) {
125  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing parenthesis in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
126  return qfalse;
127  }
128 
129  for ( i = 0 ; i < count ; i++ ) {
130  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
131  if ( !token[0] ) {
132  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing vector element in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
133  return qfalse;
134  }
135  v[i] = atof( token );
136  }
137 
138  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
139  if ( strcmp( token, ")" ) ) {
140  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing parenthesis in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
141  return qfalse;
142  }
143 
144  return qtrue;
145 }

148 /*
149 ===============
150 NameToAFunc
151 ===============

153 static unsigned NameToAFunc( const char *funcname )
154 {
155  if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "GT0" ) )
156  {
157  return GLS_ATEST_GT_0;
158  }
159  else if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "LT128" ) )
160  {
161  return GLS_ATEST_LT_80;
162  }
163  else if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "GE128" ) )
164  {
165  return GLS_ATEST_GE_80;
166  }
167 
168  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: invalid alphaFunc name '%s' in shader '%s'\n", funcname, shader.name );
169  return 0;
170 }

173 /*
174 ===============
175 NameToSrcBlendMode
176 ===============
177 */
178 static int NameToSrcBlendMode( const char *name )
179 {
180  if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_ONE" ) )
181  {
182  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE;
183  }
184  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_ZERO" ) )
185  {
186  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ZERO;
187  }
188  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_DST_COLOR" ) )
189  {
190  return GLS_SRCBLEND_DST_COLOR;
191  }
192  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_COLOR" ) )
193  {
194  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE_MINUS_DST_COLOR;
195  }
196  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_SRC_ALPHA" ) )
197  {
198  return GLS_SRCBLEND_SRC_ALPHA;
199  }
200  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA" ) )
201  {
202  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA;
203  }
204  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_DST_ALPHA" ) )
205  {
206  if (r_ignoreDstAlpha->integer)
207  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE;
208 
209  return GLS_SRCBLEND_DST_ALPHA;
210  }
211  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA" ) )
212  {
213  if (r_ignoreDstAlpha->integer)
214  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ZERO;
215 
216  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE_MINUS_DST_ALPHA;
217  }
218  else if ( !Q_stricmp( name, "GL_SRC_ALPHA_SATURATE" ) )
219  {
220  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ALPHA_SATURATE;
221  }
222 
223  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: unknown blend mode '%s' in shader '%s', substituting GL_ONE\n", name, shader.name );
224  return GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE;
225 }

277 /*
278 ===============
279 NameToGenFunc
280 ===============
281 */
282 static genFunc_t NameToGenFunc( const char *funcname )
283 {
284  if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "sin" ) )
285  {
286  return GF_SIN;
287  }
288  else if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "square" ) )
289  {
290  return GF_SQUARE;
291  }
292  else if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "triangle" ) )
293  {
294  return GF_TRIANGLE;
295  }
296  else if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "sawtooth" ) )
297  {
298  return GF_SAWTOOTH;
299  }
300  else if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "inversesawtooth" ) )
301  {
302  return GF_INVERSE_SAWTOOTH;
303  }
304  else if ( !Q_stricmp( funcname, "noise" ) )
305  {
306  return GF_NOISE;
307  }
308 
309  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: invalid genfunc name '%s' in shader '%s'\n", funcname, shader.name );
310  return GF_SIN;
311 }

314 /*
315 ===================
316 ParseWaveForm
317 ===================
318 */
319 static void ParseWaveForm( char **text, waveForm_t *wave )
320 {
321  char *token;
322 
323  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
324  if ( token[0] == 0 )
325  {
326  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing waveform parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
327  return;
328  }
329  wave->func = NameToGenFunc( token );
330 
331  // BASE, AMP, PHASE, FREQ
332  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
333  if ( token[0] == 0 )
334  {
335  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing waveform parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
336  return;
337  }
338  wave->base = atof( token );
339 
340  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
341  if ( token[0] == 0 )
342  {
343  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing waveform parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
344  return;
345  }
346  wave->amplitude = atof( token );
347 
348  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
349  if ( token[0] == 0 )
350  {
351  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing waveform parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
352  return;
353  }
354  wave->phase = atof( token );
355 
356  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
357  if ( token[0] == 0 )
358  {
359  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing waveform parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
360  return;
361  }
362  wave->frequency = atof( token );
363 }

366 /*
367 ===================
368 ParseTexMod
369 ===================
370 */
371 static void ParseTexMod( char *_text, shaderStage_t *stage )
372 {
373  const char *token;
374  char **text = &_text;
375  texModInfo_t *tmi;
376 
377  if ( stage->bundle[0].numTexMods == TR_MAX_TEXMODS ) {
378  ri.Error( ERR_DROP, "ERROR: too many tcMod stages in shader '%s'", shader.name );
379  return;
380  }
381 
382  tmi = &stage->bundle[0].texMods[stage->bundle[0].numTexMods];
383  stage->bundle[0].numTexMods++;
384 
385  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
386 
387  //
388  // turb
389  //
390  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "turb" ) )
391  {
392  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
393  if ( token[0] == 0 )
394  {
395  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing tcMod turb parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
396  return;
397  }
398  tmi->wave.base = atof( token );
399  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
400  if ( token[0] == 0 )
401  {
402  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing tcMod turb in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
403  return;
404  }
405  tmi->wave.amplitude = atof( token );
406  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
407  if ( token[0] == 0 )
408  {
409  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing tcMod turb in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
410  return;
411  }
412  tmi->wave.phase = atof( token );
413  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
414  if ( token[0] == 0 )
415  {
416  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing tcMod turb in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
417  return;
418  }
419  tmi->wave.frequency = atof( token );
420 
421  tmi->type = TMOD_TURBULENT;
422  }
423  //
424  // scale
425  //
426  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "scale" ) )
427  {
428  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
429  if ( token[0] == 0 )
430  {
431  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing scale parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
432  return;
433  }
434  tmi->scale[0] = atof( token );
435 
436  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
437  if ( token[0] == 0 )
438  {
439  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing scale parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
440  return;
441  }
442  tmi->scale[1] = atof( token );
443  tmi->type = TMOD_SCALE;
444  }
445  //
446  // scroll
447  //
448  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "scroll" ) )
449  {
450  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
451  if ( token[0] == 0 )
452  {
453  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing scale scroll parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
454  return;
455  }
456  tmi->scroll[0] = atof( token );
457  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
458  if ( token[0] == 0 )
459  {
460  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing scale scroll parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
461  return;
462  }
463  tmi->scroll[1] = atof( token );
464  tmi->type = TMOD_SCROLL;
465  }
466  //
467  // stretch
468  //
469  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "stretch" ) )
470  {
471  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
472  if ( token[0] == 0 )
473  {
474  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing stretch parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
475  return;
476  }
477  tmi->wave.func = NameToGenFunc( token );
478 
479  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
480  if ( token[0] == 0 )
481  {
482  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing stretch parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
483  return;
484  }
485  tmi->wave.base = atof( token );
486 
487  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
488  if ( token[0] == 0 )
489  {
490  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing stretch parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
491  return;
492  }
493  tmi->wave.amplitude = atof( token );
494 
495  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
496  if ( token[0] == 0 )
497  {
498  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing stretch parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
499  return;
500  }
501  tmi->wave.phase = atof( token );
502 
503  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
504  if ( token[0] == 0 )
505  {
506  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing stretch parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );

566  tmi->type = TMOD_TRANSFORM;
567  }
568  //
569  // rotate
570  //
571  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "rotate" ) )
572  {
573  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
574  if ( token[0] == 0 )
575  {
576  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing tcMod rotate parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );

584  //

589  else
590  {
591  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: unknown tcMod '%s' in shader '%s'\n", token, shader.name );
592  }
593 }

596 /*
597 ===================
598 ParseStage
599 ===================
600 */
601 static qboolean ParseStage( shaderStage_t *stage, char **text )
602 {
603  char *token;
604  int depthMaskBits = GLS_DEPTHMASK_TRUE, blendSrcBits = 0, blendDstBits = 0, atestBits = 0, depthFuncBits = 0;
605  qboolean depthMaskExplicit = qfalse;
606 
607  stage->active = qtrue;
608 
609  while ( 1 )
610  {
611  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qtrue );
612  if ( !token[0] )
613  {
614  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: no matching '}' found\n" );
615  return qfalse;
616  }
617 
618  if ( token[0] == '}' )
619  {
620  break;
621  }
622  //
623  // map <name>
624  //
625  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "map" ) )
626  {
627  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
628  if ( !token[0] )
629  {
630  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing parameter for 'map' keyword in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
631  return qfalse;
632  }
633 
634  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "$whiteimage" ) )
635  {
636  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.whiteImage;
637  continue;
638  }
639  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "$lightmap" ) )
640  {
641  stage->bundle[0].isLightmap = qtrue;
642  if ( shader.lightmapIndex < 0 || !tr.lightmaps ) {
643  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.whiteImage;
644  } else {
645  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.lightmaps[shader.lightmapIndex];
646  }
647  continue;
648  }
649  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "$deluxemap" ) )
650  {
651  if (!tr.worldDeluxeMapping)
652  {
653  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: shader '%s' wants a deluxe map in a map compiled without them\n", shader.name );
654  return qfalse;
655  }
656 
657  stage->bundle[0].isLightmap = qtrue;
658  if ( shader.lightmapIndex < 0 ) {
659  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.whiteImage;
660  } else {
661  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = tr.deluxemaps[shader.lightmapIndex];
662  }
663  continue;
664  }
665  else
666  {
667  imgType_t type = IMGTYPE_COLORALPHA;
668  imgFlags_t flags = IMGFLAG_NONE;
669 
670  if (!shader.noMipMaps)
671  flags |= IMGFLAG_MIPMAP;
672 
673  if (!shader.noPicMip)
674  flags |= IMGFLAG_PICMIP;
675 
676  if (stage->type == ST_NORMALMAP || stage->type == ST_NORMALPARALLAXMAP)
677  {
678  type = IMGTYPE_NORMAL;
679  flags |= IMGFLAG_NOLIGHTSCALE;
680 
681  if (stage->type == ST_NORMALPARALLAXMAP)
682  type = IMGTYPE_NORMALHEIGHT;
683  }
684  else
685  {
686  if (r_genNormalMaps->integer)
687  flags |= IMGFLAG_GENNORMALMAP;
688  }
689 
690  stage->bundle[0].image[0] = R_FindImageFile( token, type, flags );
691 
692  if ( !stage->bundle[0].image[0] )
693  {
694  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: R_FindImageFile could not find '%s' in shader '%s'\n", token, shader.name );
695  return qfalse;
696  }
697  }
698  }
699  //
700  // clampmap <name>
701  //
702  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "clampmap" ) )

1355  else
1356  {
1357  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: unknown parameter '%s' in shader '%s'\n", token, shader.name );
1358  return qfalse;
1359  }
1360  }
1361 
1362  //
1363  // if cgen isn't explicitly specified, use either identity or identitylighting
1364  //
1365  if ( stage->rgbGen == CGEN_BAD ) {
1366  if ( blendSrcBits == 0 ||
1367  blendSrcBits == GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE ||
1368  blendSrcBits == GLS_SRCBLEND_SRC_ALPHA ) {
1369  stage->rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY_LIGHTING;
1370  } else {
1371  stage->rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY;
1372  }
1373  }
1374 
1375 
1376  //
1377  // implicitly assume that a GL_ONE GL_ZERO blend mask disables blending
1378  //
1379  if ( ( blendSrcBits == GLS_SRCBLEND_ONE ) &&
1380  ( blendDstBits == GLS_DSTBLEND_ZERO ) )
1381  {
1382  blendDstBits = blendSrcBits = 0;
1383  depthMaskBits = GLS_DEPTHMASK_TRUE;
1384  }
1385 
1386  // decide which agens we can skip
1387  if ( stage->alphaGen == AGEN_IDENTITY ) {
1388  if ( stage->rgbGen == CGEN_IDENTITY
1389  || stage->rgbGen == CGEN_LIGHTING_DIFFUSE ) {
1390  stage->alphaGen = AGEN_SKIP;
1391  }
1392  }
1393 
1394  //
1395  // compute state bits
1396  //
1397  stage->stateBits = depthMaskBits |
1398  blendSrcBits | blendDstBits |
1399  atestBits |
1400  depthFuncBits;
1401 
1402  return qtrue;
1403 }
1404 
1405 /*
1406 ===============
1407 ParseDeform
1408 
1409 deformVertexes wave <spread> <waveform> <base> <amplitude> <phase> <frequency>
1410 deformVertexes normal <frequency> <amplitude>
1411 deformVertexes move <vector> <waveform> <base> <amplitude> <phase> <frequency>
1412 deformVertexes bulge <bulgeWidth> <bulgeHeight> <bulgeSpeed>
1413 deformVertexes projectionShadow
1414 deformVertexes autoSprite
1415 deformVertexes autoSprite2
1416 deformVertexes text[0-7]
1417 ===============
1418 */
1419 static void ParseDeform( char **text ) {
1420  char *token;
1421  deformStage_t *ds;
1422 
1423  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1424  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1425  {
1426  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deform parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1427  return;
1428  }
1429 
1430  if ( shader.numDeforms == MAX_SHADER_DEFORMS ) {
1431  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: MAX_SHADER_DEFORMS in '%s'\n", shader.name );
1432  return;
1433  }
1434 
1435  ds = &shader.deforms[ shader.numDeforms ];
1436  shader.numDeforms++;
1437 
1438  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "projectionShadow" ) ) {
1439  ds->deformation = DEFORM_PROJECTION_SHADOW;
1440  return;
1441  }
1442 
1443  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "autosprite" ) ) {
1444  ds->deformation = DEFORM_AUTOSPRITE;
1445  return;
1446  }
1447 
1448  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "autosprite2" ) ) {
1449  ds->deformation = DEFORM_AUTOSPRITE2;
1450  return;
1451  }
1452 
1453  if ( !Q_stricmpn( token, "text", 4 ) ) {
1454  int n;
1455 
1456  n = token[4] - '0';
1457  if ( n < 0 || n > 7 ) {
1458  n = 0;
1459  }
1460  ds->deformation = DEFORM_TEXT0 + n;
1461  return;
1462  }
1463 
1464  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "bulge" ) ) {
1465  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1466  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1467  {
1468  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deformVertexes bulge parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1469  return;
1470  }
1471  ds->bulgeWidth = atof( token );
1472 
1473  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1474  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1475  {
1476  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deformVertexes bulge parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1477  return;
1478  }
1479  ds->bulgeHeight = atof( token );
1480 
1481  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1482  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1483  {
1484  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deformVertexes bulge parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1485  return;
1486  }
1487  ds->bulgeSpeed = atof( token );
1488 
1489  ds->deformation = DEFORM_BULGE;
1490  return;
1491  }
1492 
1493  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "wave" ) )
1494  {
1495  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1496  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1497  {
1498  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deformVertexes parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1499  return;
1500  }
1501 
1502  if ( atof( token ) != 0 )
1503  {
1504  ds->deformationSpread = 1.0f / atof( token );
1505  }
1506  else
1507  {
1508  ds->deformationSpread = 100.0f;
1509  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: illegal div value of 0 in deformVertexes command for shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1510  }
1511 
1512  ParseWaveForm( text, &ds->deformationWave );
1513  ds->deformation = DEFORM_WAVE;
1514  return;
1515  }
1516 
1517  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "normal" ) )
1518  {
1519  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1520  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1521  {
1522  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deformVertexes parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1523  return;
1524  }
1525  ds->deformationWave.amplitude = atof( token );
1526 
1527  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1528  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1529  {
1530  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deformVertexes parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1531  return;
1532  }
1533  ds->deformationWave.frequency = atof( token );
1534 
1535  ds->deformation = DEFORM_NORMALS;
1536  return;
1537  }
1538 
1539  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "move" ) ) {
1540  int i;
1541 
1542  for ( i = 0 ; i < 3 ; i++ ) {
1543  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1544  if ( token[0] == 0 ) {
1545  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing deformVertexes parm in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1546  return;
1547  }
1548  ds->moveVector[i] = atof( token );
1549  }
1550 
1551  ParseWaveForm( text, &ds->deformationWave );
1552  ds->deformation = DEFORM_MOVE;
1553  return;
1554  }
1555 
1556  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: unknown deformVertexes subtype '%s' found in shader '%s'\n", token, shader.name );
1557 }

1614  , token, suf[i] );
1615  shader.sky.innerbox[i] = R_FindImageFile( ( char * ) pathname, IMGTYPE_COLORALPHA, imgFlags );
1616  if ( !shader.sky.innerbox[i] ) {
1617  shader.sky.innerbox[i] = tr.defaultImage;
1618  }
1619  }
1620  }
1621 
1622  shader.isSky = qtrue;
1623 }

1743 /*
1744 =================
1745 ParseShader
1746 
1747 The current text pointer is at the explicit text definition of the
1748 shader. Parse it into the global shader variable. Later functions
1749 will optimize it.
1750 =================
1751 */
1752 static qboolean ParseShader( char **text )
1753 {
1754  char *token;
1755  int s;
1756 
1757  s = 0;
1758 
1759  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qtrue );
1760  if ( token[0] != '{' )
1761  {
1762  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: expecting '{', found '%s' instead in shader '%s'\n", token, shader.name );
1763  return qfalse;
1764  }
1765 
1766  while ( 1 )
1767  {
1768  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qtrue );
1769  if ( !token[0] )
1770  {
1771  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: no concluding '}' in shader %s\n", shader.name );
1772  return qfalse;
1773  }
1774 
1775  // end of shader definition
1776  if ( token[0] == '}' )
1777  {
1778  break;
1779  }
1780  // stage definition
1781  else if ( token[0] == '{' )
1782  {
1783  if ( s >= MAX_SHADER_STAGES ) {
1784  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: too many stages in shader %s (max is %i)\n", shader.name, MAX_SHADER_STAGES );
1785  return qfalse;
1786  }
1787 
1788  if ( !ParseStage( &stages[s], text ) )
1789  {
1790  return qfalse;
1791  }
1792  stages[s].active = qtrue;
1793  s++;
1794 
1795  continue;
1796  }
1797  // skip stuff that only the QuakeEdRadient needs
1798  else if ( !Q_stricmpn( token, "qer", 3 ) ) {
1799  SkipRestOfLine( text );
1800  continue;
1801  }
1802  // sun parms
1803  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "q3map_sun" ) || !Q_stricmp( token, "q3map_sunExt" ) || !Q_stricmp( token, "q3gl2_sun" ) ) {
1804  float a, b;
1805  qboolean isGL2Sun = qfalse;
1806 
1807  if (!Q_stricmp( token, "q3gl2_sun" ) && r_sunShadows->integer )
1808  {
1809  isGL2Sun = qtrue;
1810  tr.sunShadows = qtrue;
1811  }
1812 
1813  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1814  tr.sunLight[0] = atof( token );
1815  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1816  tr.sunLight[1] = atof( token );
1817  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1818  tr.sunLight[2] = atof( token );
1819 
1820  VectorNormalize( tr.sunLight );
1821 
1822  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1823  a = atof( token );
1824  VectorScale( tr.sunLight, a, tr.sunLight);
1825 
1826  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1827  a = atof( token );
1828  a = a / 180 * M_PI;
1829 
1830  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1831  b = atof( token );
1832  b = b / 180 * M_PI;
1833 
1834  tr.sunDirection[0] = cos( a ) * cos( b );
1835  tr.sunDirection[1] = sin( a ) * cos( b );
1836  tr.sunDirection[2] = sin( b );
1837 
1838  if (isGL2Sun)
1839  {
1840  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1841  tr.sunShadowScale = atof(token);
1842 
1843  // parse twice, since older shaders may include mapLightScale before sunShadowScale
1844  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1845  if (token[0])
1846  tr.sunShadowScale = atof(token);
1847  }
1848 
1849  SkipRestOfLine( text );
1850  continue;
1851  }
1852  // tonemap parms
1853  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "q3gl2_tonemap" ) ) {
1854  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1855  tr.toneMinAvgMaxLevel[0] = atof( token );
1856  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1857  tr.toneMinAvgMaxLevel[1] = atof( token );
1858  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1859  tr.toneMinAvgMaxLevel[2] = atof( token );
1860 
1861  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1862  tr.autoExposureMinMax[0] = atof( token );
1863  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1864  tr.autoExposureMinMax[1] = atof( token );
1865 
1866  SkipRestOfLine( text );
1867  continue;
1868  }
1869  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "deformVertexes" ) ) {
1870  ParseDeform( text );
1871  continue;
1872  }
1873  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "tesssize" ) ) {
1874  SkipRestOfLine( text );
1875  continue;
1876  }
1877  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "clampTime" ) ) {
1878  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1879  if (token[0]) {
1880  shader.clampTime = atof(token);
1881  }
1882  }
1883  // skip stuff that only the q3map needs
1884  else if ( !Q_stricmpn( token, "q3map", 5 ) ) {
1885  SkipRestOfLine( text );
1886  continue;
1887  }
1888  // skip stuff that only q3map or the server needs
1889  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "surfaceParm" ) ) {
1890  ParseSurfaceParm( text );
1891  continue;
1892  }
1893  // no mip maps
1894  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "nomipmaps" ) )
1895  {
1896  shader.noMipMaps = qtrue;
1897  shader.noPicMip = qtrue;
1898  continue;
1899  }
1900  // no picmip adjustment
1901  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "nopicmip" ) )
1902  {
1903  shader.noPicMip = qtrue;
1904  continue;
1905  }
1906  // polygonOffset
1907  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "polygonOffset" ) )
1908  {
1909  shader.polygonOffset = qtrue;
1910  continue;
1911  }
1912  // entityMergable, allowing sprite surfaces from multiple entities
1913  // to be merged into one batch. This is a savings for smoke
1914  // puffs and blood, but can't be used for anything where the
1915  // shader calcs (not the surface function) reference the entity color or scroll
1916  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "entityMergable" ) )
1917  {
1918  shader.entityMergable = qtrue;
1919  continue;
1920  }
1921  // fogParms
1922  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "fogParms" ) )
1923  {
1924  if ( !ParseVector( text, 3, shader.fogParms.color ) ) {
1925  return qfalse;
1926  }
1927 
1928  if ( r_greyscale->integer )
1929  {
1930  float luminance;
1931 
1932  luminance = LUMA( shader.fogParms.color[0], shader.fogParms.color[1], shader.fogParms.color[2] );
1933  VectorSet( shader.fogParms.color, luminance, luminance, luminance );
1934  }
1935  else if ( r_greyscale->value )
1936  {
1937  float luminance;
1938 
1939  luminance = LUMA( shader.fogParms.color[0], shader.fogParms.color[1], shader.fogParms.color[2] );
1940  shader.fogParms.color[0] = LERP( shader.fogParms.color[0], luminance, r_greyscale->value );
1941  shader.fogParms.color[1] = LERP( shader.fogParms.color[1], luminance, r_greyscale->value );
1942  shader.fogParms.color[2] = LERP( shader.fogParms.color[2], luminance, r_greyscale->value );
1943  }
1944 
1945  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1946  if ( !token[0] )
1947  {
1948  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing parm for 'fogParms' keyword in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1949  continue;
1950  }
1951  shader.fogParms.depthForOpaque = atof( token );
1952 
1953  // skip any old gradient directions
1954  SkipRestOfLine( text );
1955  continue;
1956  }
1957  // portal
1958  else if ( !Q_stricmp(token, "portal") )
1959  {
1960  shader.sort = SS_PORTAL;
1961  shader.isPortal = qtrue;
1962  continue;
1963  }
1964  // skyparms <cloudheight> <outerbox> <innerbox>
1965  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "skyparms" ) )
1966  {
1967  ParseSkyParms( text );
1968  continue;
1969  }
1970  // light <value> determines flaring in q3map, not needed here
1971  else if ( !Q_stricmp(token, "light") )
1972  {
1973  COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1974  continue;
1975  }
1976  // cull <face>
1977  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "cull") )
1978  {
1979  token = COM_ParseExt( text, qfalse );
1980  if ( token[0] == 0 )
1981  {
1982  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: missing cull parms in shader '%s'\n", shader.name );
1983  continue;
1984  }
1985 
1986  if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "none" ) || !Q_stricmp( token, "twosided" ) || !Q_stricmp( token, "disable" ) )
1987  {
1988  shader.cullType = CT_TWO_SIDED;
1989  }
1990  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "back" ) || !Q_stricmp( token, "backside" ) || !Q_stricmp( token, "backsided" ) )
1991  {
1992  shader.cullType = CT_BACK_SIDED;
1993  }
1994  else
1995  {
1996  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: invalid cull parm '%s' in shader '%s'\n", token, shader.name );
1997  }
1998  continue;
1999  }
2000  // sort
2001  else if ( !Q_stricmp( token, "sort" ) )
2002  {
2003  ParseSort( text );
2004  continue;
2005  }
2006  else
2007  {
2008  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: unknown general shader parameter '%s' in '%s'\n", token, shader.name );
2009  return qfalse;
2010  }
2011  }
2012 
2013  //
2014  // ignore shaders that don't have any stages, unless it is a sky or fog
2015  //
2016  if ( s == 0 && !shader.isSky && !(shader.contentFlags & CONTENTS_FOG ) ) {
2017  return qfalse;
2018  }
2019 
2020  shader.explicitlyDefined = qtrue;
2021 
2022  return qtrue;
2023 }

2335 static int CollapseStagesToGLSL(void)
2336 {
2337  int i, j, numStages;
2338  qboolean skip = qfalse;
2339 
2340  // skip shaders with deforms
2341  if (shader.numDeforms != 0)
2342  {
2343  skip = qtrue;
2344  }
2345 
2346  if (!skip)
2347  {
2348  // if 2+ stages and first stage is lightmap, switch them
2349  // this makes it easier for the later bits to process
2350  if (stages[0].active && stages[0].bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_LIGHTMAP && stages[1].active)
2351  {
2352  int blendBits = stages[1].stateBits & ( GLS_DSTBLEND_BITS | GLS_SRCBLEND_BITS );
2353 
2354  if (blendBits == (GLS_DSTBLEND_SRC_COLOR | GLS_SRCBLEND_ZERO)
2355  || blendBits == (GLS_DSTBLEND_ZERO | GLS_SRCBLEND_DST_COLOR))
2356  {
2357  int stateBits0 = stages[0].stateBits;
2358  int stateBits1 = stages[1].stateBits;
2359  shaderStage_t swapStage;
2360 
2361  swapStage = stages[0];
2362  stages[0] = stages[1];
2363  stages[1] = swapStage;
2364 
2365  stages[0].stateBits = stateBits0;
2366  stages[1].stateBits = stateBits1;
2367  }
2368  }
2369  }
2370 
2371  if (!skip)
2372  {
2373  // scan for shaders that aren't supported
2374  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
2375  {
2376  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[i];
2377 
2378  if (!pStage->active)
2379  continue;
2380 
2381  if (pStage->adjustColorsForFog)
2382  {
2383  skip = qtrue;
2384  break;
2385  }
2386 
2387  if (pStage->bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_LIGHTMAP)
2388  {
2389  int blendBits = pStage->stateBits & ( GLS_DSTBLEND_BITS | GLS_SRCBLEND_BITS );
2390 
2391  if (blendBits != (GLS_DSTBLEND_SRC_COLOR | GLS_SRCBLEND_ZERO)
2392  && blendBits != (GLS_DSTBLEND_ZERO | GLS_SRCBLEND_DST_COLOR))
2393  {
2394  skip = qtrue;
2395  break;
2396  }
2397  }
2398 
2399  switch(pStage->bundle[0].tcGen)
2400  {
2401  case TCGEN_TEXTURE:
2402  case TCGEN_LIGHTMAP:
2403  case TCGEN_ENVIRONMENT_MAPPED:
2404  case TCGEN_VECTOR:
2405  break;
2406  default:
2407  skip = qtrue;
2408  break;
2409  }
2410 
2411  switch(pStage->alphaGen)
2412  {
2413  case AGEN_LIGHTING_SPECULAR:
2414  case AGEN_PORTAL:
2415  skip = qtrue;
2416  break;
2417  default:
2418  break;
2419  }
2420  }
2421  }
2422 
2423  if (!skip)
2424  {
2425  qboolean usedLightmap = qfalse;
2426 
2427  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
2428  {
2429  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[i];
2430  shaderStage_t *diffuse, *normal, *specular, *lightmap;
2431  qboolean parallax, tcgen, diffuselit, vertexlit;
2432 
2433  if (!pStage->active)
2434  continue;
2435 
2436  // skip normal and specular maps
2437  if (pStage->type != ST_COLORMAP)
2438  continue;
2439 
2440  // skip lightmaps
2441  if (pStage->bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_LIGHTMAP)
2442  continue;
2443 
2444  diffuse = pStage;
2445  normal = NULL;
2446  parallax = qfalse;
2447  specular = NULL;
2448  lightmap = NULL;
2449 
2450  // we have a diffuse map, find matching normal, specular, and lightmap
2451  for (j = i + 1; j < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; j++)
2452  {
2453  shaderStage_t *pStage2 = &stages[j];
2454 
2455  if (!pStage2->active)
2456  continue;
2457 
2458  switch(pStage2->type)
2459  {
2460  case ST_NORMALMAP:
2461  if (!normal)
2462  {
2463  normal = pStage2;
2464  }
2465  break;
2466 
2467  case ST_NORMALPARALLAXMAP:
2468  if (!normal)
2469  {
2470  normal = pStage2;
2471  parallax = qtrue;
2472  }
2473  break;
2474 
2475  case ST_SPECULARMAP:
2476  if (!specular)
2477  {
2478  specular = pStage2;
2479  }
2480  break;
2481 
2482  case ST_COLORMAP:
2483  if (pStage2->bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_LIGHTMAP)
2484  {
2485  int blendBits = pStage->stateBits & ( GLS_DSTBLEND_BITS | GLS_SRCBLEND_BITS );
2486 
2487  // Only add lightmap to blendfunc filter stage if it's the first time lightmap is used
2488  // otherwise it will cause the shader to be darkened by the lightmap multiple times.
2489  if (!usedLightmap || (blendBits != (GLS_DSTBLEND_SRC_COLOR | GLS_SRCBLEND_ZERO)
2490  && blendBits != (GLS_DSTBLEND_ZERO | GLS_SRCBLEND_DST_COLOR)))
2491  {
2492  lightmap = pStage2;
2493  usedLightmap = qtrue;
2494  }
2495  }
2496  break;
2497 
2498  default:
2499  break;
2500  }
2501  }
2502 
2503  tcgen = qfalse;
2504  if (diffuse->bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_ENVIRONMENT_MAPPED
2505  || diffuse->bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_LIGHTMAP
2506  || diffuse->bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_VECTOR)
2507  {
2508  tcgen = qtrue;
2509  }
2510 
2511  diffuselit = qfalse;
2512  if (diffuse->rgbGen == CGEN_LIGHTING_DIFFUSE)
2513  {
2514  diffuselit = qtrue;
2515  }
2516 
2517  vertexlit = qfalse;
2518  if (diffuse->rgbGen == CGEN_VERTEX_LIT || diffuse->rgbGen == CGEN_EXACT_VERTEX_LIT)
2519  {
2520  vertexlit = qtrue;
2521  }
2522 
2523  CollapseStagesToLightall(diffuse, normal, specular, lightmap, diffuselit, vertexlit, parallax, tcgen);
2524  }
2525 
2526  // deactivate lightmap stages
2527  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
2528  {
2529  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[i];
2530 
2531  if (!pStage->active)
2532  continue;
2533 
2534  if (pStage->bundle[0].tcGen == TCGEN_LIGHTMAP)
2535  {
2536  pStage->active = qfalse;
2537  }
2538  }
2539  }
2540 
2541  // deactivate normal and specular stages
2542  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
2543  {
2544  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[i];
2545 
2546  if (!pStage->active)
2547  continue;
2548 
2549  if (pStage->type == ST_NORMALMAP)
2550  {
2551  pStage->active = qfalse;
2552  }
2553 
2554  if (pStage->type == ST_NORMALPARALLAXMAP)
2555  {
2556  pStage->active = qfalse;
2557  }
2558 
2559  if (pStage->type == ST_SPECULARMAP)
2560  {
2561  pStage->active = qfalse;
2562  }
2563  }
2564 
2565  // remove inactive stages
2566  numStages = 0;
2567  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
2568  {
2569  if (!stages[i].active)
2570  continue;
2571 
2572  if (i == numStages)
2573  {
2574  numStages++;
2575  continue;
2576  }
2577 
2578  stages[numStages] = stages[i];
2579  stages[i].active = qfalse;
2580  numStages++;
2581  }
2582 
2583  // convert any remaining lightmap stages to a lighting pass with a white texture
2584  // only do this with r_sunlightMode non-zero, as it's only for correct shadows.
2585  if (r_sunlightMode->integer && shader.numDeforms == 0)
2586  {
2587  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
2588  {
2589  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[i];
2590 
2591  if (!pStage->active)
2592  continue;
2593 
2594  if (pStage->adjustColorsForFog)
2595  continue;
2596 
2597  if (pStage->bundle[TB_DIFFUSEMAP].tcGen == TCGEN_LIGHTMAP)
2598  {
2599  pStage->glslShaderGroup = tr.lightallShader;
2600  pStage->glslShaderIndex = LIGHTDEF_USE_LIGHTMAP;
2601  pStage->bundle[TB_LIGHTMAP] = pStage->bundle[TB_DIFFUSEMAP];
2602  pStage->bundle[TB_DIFFUSEMAP].image[0] = tr.whiteImage;
2603  pStage->bundle[TB_DIFFUSEMAP].isLightmap = qfalse;
2604  pStage->bundle[TB_DIFFUSEMAP].tcGen = TCGEN_TEXTURE;
2605  }
2606  }
2607  }
2608 
2609  // convert any remaining lightingdiffuse stages to a lighting pass
2610  if (shader.numDeforms == 0)
2611  {
2612  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; i++)
2613  {
2614  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[i];
2615 
2616  if (!pStage->active)
2617  continue;
2618 
2619  if (pStage->adjustColorsForFog)
2620  continue;
2621 
2622  if (pStage->rgbGen == CGEN_LIGHTING_DIFFUSE)
2623  {
2624  pStage->glslShaderGroup = tr.lightallShader;
2625  pStage->glslShaderIndex = LIGHTDEF_USE_LIGHT_VECTOR;
2626 
2627  if (pStage->bundle[0].tcGen != TCGEN_TEXTURE || pStage->bundle[0].numTexMods != 0)
2628  pStage->glslShaderIndex |= LIGHTDEF_USE_TCGEN_AND_TCMOD;
2629  }
2630  }
2631  }
2632 
2633  return numStages;
2634 }

2636 /*
2637 =============
2638 
2639 FixRenderCommandList
2640 https://zerowing.idsoftware.com/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=493
2641 Arnout: this is a nasty issue. Shaders can be registered after drawsurfaces are generated
2642 but before the frame is rendered. This will, for the duration of one frame, cause drawsurfaces
2643 to be rendered with bad shaders. To fix this, need to go through all render commands and fix
2644 sortedIndex.
2645 ==============
2646 */
2647 static void FixRenderCommandList( int newShader ) {
2648  renderCommandList_t *cmdList = &backEndData->commands;
2649 
2650  if( cmdList ) {
2651  const void *curCmd = cmdList->cmds;
2652 
2653  while ( 1 ) {
2654  curCmd = PADP(curCmd, sizeof(void *));
2655 
2656  switch ( *(const int *)curCmd ) {
2657  case RC_SET_COLOR:
2658  {
2659  const setColorCommand_t *sc_cmd = (const setColorCommand_t *)curCmd;
2660  curCmd = (const void *)(sc_cmd + 1);
2661  break;
2662  }
2663  case RC_STRETCH_PIC:
2664  {
2665  const stretchPicCommand_t *sp_cmd = (const stretchPicCommand_t *)curCmd;

2804 /*
2805 =================
2806 VertexLightingCollapse
2807 
2808 If vertex lighting is enabled, only render a single
2809 pass, trying to guess which is the correct one to best approximate
2810 what it is supposed to look like.
2811 =================
2812 */
2813 static void VertexLightingCollapse( void ) {
2814  int stage;
2815  shaderStage_t *bestStage;
2816  int bestImageRank;
2817  int rank;
2818 
2819  // if we aren't opaque, just use the first pass
2820  if ( shader.sort == SS_OPAQUE ) {
2821 
2822  // pick the best texture for the single pass
2823  bestStage = &stages[0];
2824  bestImageRank = -999999;
2825 
2826  for ( stage = 0; stage < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; stage++ ) {
2827  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[stage];
2828 
2829  if ( !pStage->active ) {
2830  break;
2831  }
2832  rank = 0;
2833 
2834  if ( pStage->bundle[0].isLightmap ) {
2835  rank -= 100;
2836  }
2837  if ( pStage->bundle[0].tcGen != TCGEN_TEXTURE ) {
2838  rank -= 5;
2839  }
2840  if ( pStage->bundle[0].numTexMods ) {
2841  rank -= 5;
2842  }
2843  if ( pStage->rgbGen != CGEN_IDENTITY && pStage->rgbGen != CGEN_IDENTITY_LIGHTING ) {
2844  rank -= 3;
2845  }
2846 
2847  if ( rank > bestImageRank ) {
2848  bestImageRank = rank;
2849  bestStage = pStage;
2850  }
2851  }
2852 
2853  stages[0].bundle[0] = bestStage->bundle[0];
2854  stages[0].stateBits &= ~( GLS_DSTBLEND_BITS | GLS_SRCBLEND_BITS );
2855  stages[0].stateBits |= GLS_DEPTHMASK_TRUE;
2856  if ( shader.lightmapIndex == LIGHTMAP_NONE ) {
2857  stages[0].rgbGen = CGEN_LIGHTING_DIFFUSE;
2858  } else {
2859  stages[0].rgbGen = CGEN_EXACT_VERTEX;
2860  }
2861  stages[0].alphaGen = AGEN_SKIP;
2862  } else {
2863  // don't use a lightmap (tesla coils)
2864  if ( stages[0].bundle[0].isLightmap ) {
2865  stages[0] = stages[1];
2866  }
2867 
2868  // if we were in a cross-fade cgen, hack it to normal
2869  if ( stages[0].rgbGen == CGEN_ONE_MINUS_ENTITY || stages[1].rgbGen == CGEN_ONE_MINUS_ENTITY ) {
2870  stages[0].rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY_LIGHTING;
2871  }
2872  if ( ( stages[0].rgbGen == CGEN_WAVEFORM && stages[0].rgbWave.func == GF_SAWTOOTH )
2873  && ( stages[1].rgbGen == CGEN_WAVEFORM && stages[1].rgbWave.func == GF_INVERSE_SAWTOOTH ) ) {
2874  stages[0].rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY_LIGHTING;
2875  }
2876  if ( ( stages[0].rgbGen == CGEN_WAVEFORM && stages[0].rgbWave.func == GF_INVERSE_SAWTOOTH )
2877  && ( stages[1].rgbGen == CGEN_WAVEFORM && stages[1].rgbWave.func == GF_SAWTOOTH ) ) {
2878  stages[0].rgbGen = CGEN_IDENTITY_LIGHTING;
2879  }
2880  }
2881 
2882  for ( stage = 1; stage < MAX_SHADER_STAGES; stage++ ) {
2883  shaderStage_t *pStage = &stages[stage];
2884 
2885  if ( !pStage->active ) {
2886  break;
2887  }
2888 
2889  Com_Memset( pStage, 0, sizeof( *pStage ) );
2890  }
2891 }

3650 /*
3651 ====================
3652 ScanAndLoadShaderFiles
3653 
3654 Finds and loads all .shader files, combining them into
3655 a single large text block that can be scanned for shader names
3656 =====================
3657 */
3658 #define MAX_SHADER_FILES 4096
3659 static void ScanAndLoadShaderFiles( void )
3660 {
3661  char **shaderFiles;
3662  char *buffers[MAX_SHADER_FILES] = {NULL};
3663  char *p;
3664  int numShaderFiles;
3665  int i;
3666  char *oldp, *token, *hashMem, *textEnd;
3667  int shaderTextHashTableSizes[MAX_SHADERTEXT_HASH], hash, size;
3668  char shaderName[MAX_QPATH];
3669  int shaderLine;
3670 
3671  long sum = 0, summand;
3672  // scan for shader files
3673  shaderFiles = ri.FS_ListFiles( "scripts", ".shader", &numShaderFiles );
3674 
3675  if ( !shaderFiles || !numShaderFiles )
3676  {
3677  ri.Printf( PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: no shader files found\n" );
3678  return;
3679  }
3680 
3681  if ( numShaderFiles > MAX_SHADER_FILES ) {
3682  numShaderFiles = MAX_SHADER_FILES;
3683  }
3684 
3685  // load and parse shader files
3686  for ( i = 0; i < numShaderFiles; i++ )
3687  {
3688  char filename[MAX_QPATH];
3689 
3690  // look for a .mtr file first
3691  {
3692  char *ext;
3693  Com_sprintf( filename, sizeof( filename ), "scripts/%s", shaderFiles[i] );
3694  if ( (ext = strrchr(filename, '.')) )
3695  {
3696  strcpy(ext, ".mtr");
3697  }
3698 
3699  if ( ri.FS_ReadFile( filename, NULL ) <= 0 )
3700  {
3701  Com_sprintf( filename, sizeof( filename ), "scripts/%s", shaderFiles[i] );
3702  }
3703  }
3704 
3705  ri.Printf( PRINT_DEVELOPER, "...loading '%s'\n", filename );
3706  summand = ri.FS_ReadFile( filename, (void **)&buffers[i] );
3707 
3708  if ( !buffers[i] )
3709  ri.Error( ERR_DROP, "Couldn't load %s", filename );
3710 
3711  // Do a simple check on the shader structure in that file to make sure one bad shader file cannot fuck up all other shaders.
3712  p = buffers[i];
3713  COM_BeginParseSession(filename);
3714  while(1)
3715  {
3716  token = COM_ParseExt(&p, qtrue);
3717 
3718  if(!*token)
3719  break;
3720 
3721  Q_strncpyz(shaderName, token, sizeof(shaderName));
3722  shaderLine = COM_GetCurrentParseLine();
3723 
3724  token = COM_ParseExt(&p, qtrue);
3725  if(token[0] != '{' || token[1] != '\0')
3726  {
3727  ri.Printf(PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: Ignoring shader file %s. Shader \"%s\" on line %d missing opening brace",
3728  filename, shaderName, shaderLine);
3729  if (token[0])
3730  {
3731  ri.Printf(PRINT_WARNING, " (found \"%s\" on line %d)", token, COM_GetCurrentParseLine());
3732  }
3733  ri.Printf(PRINT_WARNING, ".\n");
3734  ri.FS_FreeFile(buffers[i]);
3735  buffers[i] = NULL;
3736  break;
3737  }
3738 
3739  if(!SkipBracedSection(&p, 1))
3740  {
3741  ri.Printf(PRINT_WARNING, "WARNING: Ignoring shader file %s. Shader \"%s\" on line %d missing closing brace.\n",
3742  filename, shaderName, shaderLine);
3743  ri.FS_FreeFile(buffers[i]);
3744  buffers[i] = NULL;
3745  break;
3746  }
3747  }
3748 
3749 
3750  if (buffers[i])
3751  sum += summand;
3752  }
3753 
3754  // build single large buffer
3755  s_shaderText = ri.Hunk_Alloc( sum + numShaderFiles*2, h_low );
3756  s_shaderText[ 0 ] = '\0';
3757  textEnd = s_shaderText;
3758 
3759  // free in reverse order, so the temp files are all dumped
3760  for ( i = numShaderFiles - 1; i >= 0 ; i-- )
3761  {
3762  if ( !buffers[i] )
3763  continue;
3764 
3765  strcat( textEnd, buffers[i] );
3766  strcat( textEnd, "\n" );
3767  textEnd += strlen( textEnd );
3768  ri.FS_FreeFile( buffers[i] );
3769  }
3770 
3771  COM_Compress( s_shaderText );
3772 
3773  // free up memory
3774  ri.FS_FreeFileList( shaderFiles );
3775 
3776  Com_Memset(shaderTextHashTableSizes, 0, sizeof(shaderTextHashTableSizes));
3777  size = 0;
3778 
3779  p = s_shaderText;
3780  // look for shader names
3781  while ( 1 ) {
3782  token = COM_ParseExt( &p, qtrue );
3783  if ( token[0] == 0 ) {
3784  break;
3785  }
3786 
3787  hash = generateHashValue(token, MAX_SHADERTEXT_HASH);
3788  shaderTextHashTableSizes[hash]++;
3789  size++;
3790  SkipBracedSection(&p, 0);
3791  }
3792 
3793  size += MAX_SHADERTEXT_HASH;
3794 
3795  hashMem = ri.Hunk_Alloc( size * sizeof(char *), h_low );
3796 
3797  for (i = 0; i < MAX_SHADERTEXT_HASH; i++) {
3798  shaderTextHashTable[i] = (char **) hashMem;
3799  hashMem = ((char *) hashMem) + ((shaderTextHashTableSizes[i] + 1) * sizeof(char *));
3800  }
3801 
3802  Com_Memset(shaderTextHashTableSizes, 0, sizeof(shaderTextHashTableSizes));
3803 
3804  p = s_shaderText;
3805  // look for shader names
3806  while ( 1 ) {
3807  oldp = p;
3808  token = COM_ParseExt( &p, qtrue );
3809  if ( token[0] == 0 ) {
3810  break;
3811  }
3812 
3813  hash = generateHashValue(token, MAX_SHADERTEXT_HASH);
3814  shaderTextHashTable[hash][shaderTextHashTableSizes[hash]++] = oldp;
3815 
3816  SkipBracedSection(&p, 0);
3817  }
3818 
3819  return;
3820 
3821 }
